JOHANNESBURG â€“ At least one person has died and another two people have been wounded in a shooting at East Rand Mall in Boksburg on Friday afternoon. The incident took place shortly after noon. It is claimed police received a tip-off that the suspects, wanted in connection with murder, were at the mall. When the suspects saw police, a shootout ensued. Eyewitnesses earlier claimed that an armed robbery had taken place at the shopping complex. One of those wounded was a suspect while another was arrested, police said. Paramedics at the scene said a guard was killed while a female shopper was also caught in the gunfire. Earlier, a chopper landed at the mall to transport one of those wounded to hospital. Police said three suspects were on the run. eNCA